ce:section.ce:para:
Based on the preceding results, we surmised that DhHP-6 might inhibit Aβ aggregation by changing its secondary structure. The effect of DhHP-6 on the conformational changes in Aβ1–42 were assessed by CD spectrometry. Pure Aβ1–42 and DhHP-6 mixed with Aβ1–42 were assessed at 0 and 72 h. The initial secondary structure of Aβ1–42 was less α-helical, composed mainly of β-sheets and random coils with a strong CD signal at 197 nm (Fig. 6
                        A). After a 72-h incubation with DhHP-6, there remained only a weak CD signal at approximately 197 nm, clearly indicating that DhHP-6 reduced β-sheet structures (Fig. 6B). The percentage of β-sheets was reduced from 89.1% to 78.3% by DhHP-6 (Table 1
                        ).
